<br>
This is my first post to this board.  I have been reading the board for weeks now in anticipation of reading about somebody achieving the &quot;best&quot; sword in the game.  After all the hype, I am very disappointed in both the sword and the quest itself.  <br>
<br>
First of all, the sword is a two handed sword.  Personally, I love to use a shield and with a two handed sword, it is now impossible.  Granted, the damage of the sword is nice but I don't like the delay at all.  The proc is nice, but again, it's a two handed sword.  I was hoping and praying that the sword would be one handed but I guess I've been let down again by Verant (I agree with an earlier statement that somebody made saying that Brad and Verant have no clue...).<br>
<br>
Secondly, the quest is extremely hard to do and you basically have to be rich, 46+ in level, and have a lot of friends with you (granted that Drool's guild is very small and he still managed to do it).  I expected the quest to be very hard but not like this.  I mean, come on, two dragons have to be killed and the books are rare drops...that's a little extreme.  Now that they have to be slain for their items, they will be camped more frequently, thus making it harder to get the items.  Maybe the &quot;play nice&quot; policy will help this situation (*dripping with sarcasm*).<br>
<br>
After knowing all this info, I probably won't even waste my time questing for this item.  I am totally disgusted in this quest now.  I feel as though my reason for being a paladin has been ripped from me.  From the moment I created my paladin, I wanted the FA because it was THE sword for any paladin to get.  Now, it just isn't worth the time or trouble.  Again, I feel as though Verant has screwed my favorite class over (again).  I now need to find some other goal to try and obtain that will push my desire further.<br>
<br>
Trajan d'Anjou<br>
